<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 2:40PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
Surry, northwestern Stokes and northeastern Yadkin Counties through
315 PM EDT...
At 240 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bottom, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Mount Airy...
Fairview...
Flat Rock...
Dobson...
Pilot Mountain...
East Bend...
and Francisco.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
